EmailTemplate.name: DR New Year's 2016 - Final Email
EmailTemplate.subject: Get ready for your trip!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Build Volunteers,
Can you believe that in just a few short weeks you will be in the Dominican Republic?! I hope all of you know how hard you worked to get here, from fundraising, to working long hours, to choosing to spend money on this trip over the many shopping sprees you could have had. You are now almost there...
Before you take off, we have some important information and reminders. (There is a lot of important information below. Please take the time to read it thoroughly!)
1. FLIGHTS When you land in Puerto Plata, our staff will be wearing a Live Different t-shirt or holding a Live Different sign. Come find us and we'll take you back to Sosua by the Sea where you can unpack and meet the group.
2. PASSPORTS Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be given to the resort staff upon check in, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling.
3. EXCURSIONS There will be an optional excursion on your day off! Activities will be explained and announced on your first night in Dominican Republic. The costs of the full day excursion is generally between $80-90 USD.
4. EMERGENCY CONTACTS If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency while in the Dominican Republic, these are the numbers to call:
Live Different Build Office:1-866-432-4464 (toll free) Brett: 1 829 675 3684 Sosua by the Sea: 809-571-3222
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email at joy@livedifferent.com.
5. PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS
Calling cards do not work in the DR. Some past volunteers have put international plans on their cell phones prior to leaving but you will need to contact your cell service provider to see if this is possible. There is wifi available for purchase at the resort. Costs for this are $2 for an hour, $5 for a day, $25 for the 10 days (USD). Some people like to bring their laptops as well, but keep in mind that Live Different is not responsible for lost or stolen items. There are safes available in the rooms for smaller valuable items, but they are not large enough to fit most laptops.
6. SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY - It is best to bring cash in USD. Dominican Pesos are also accepted, but Canadian currency is not. - Please consider the following when deciding how much spending money to bring:
Your meals while traveling to and from your home to Puerto Plata $50 for any personal spending (for things like souvenirs or snacks) $30 USD we collect the resort staff tip and divide it evenly among each resort staff (housekeeping, kitchen staff, restaurant staff, front desk, etc.) $20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team $90 USD if you choose to participate in the day off excursion
7. PACKING LIST A packing list is attached for all who need it again. Don't forget to pack bug spray as there could be mosquito-borne illnesses.
8. YOUR LIVE DIFFERENT STAFF Brett, Katie, and Mark will be your trip hosts. They're looking forward to meeting you all! (And seeing some familiar faces!)
9. MEET THE FAMILY YOU'LL BE BUILDING FOR! I will be sending another email soon to let you know the information of the family you will be building for.
Thank you for taking the time to read through all of that very important information. If you have any questions, please feel free to send me an email or I can always give you a call.
Have a great time celebrating during this beautiful holiday season!
Joy Yu Program Administrator
